1343
01:15:34.468 --> 01:15:37.028
HENRY: <i>Then. I couldn't believe</i>
<i>what happened.</i>

1344
01:15:37.428 --> 01:15:39.988
<i>When we got home.</i>
<i>we were all over the newspaper.</i>

1345
01:15:40.068 --> 01:15:42.946
<i>At first I didn't even know why</i>
<i>we got picked up.</i>

1346
01:15:43.188 --> 01:15:45.577
<i>Then I found out the guy we roughed up...</i>

1347
01:15:45.668 --> 01:15:48.546
<i>... had a sister working as a typist</i>
<i>for the FBI.</i>

1348
01:15:48.788 --> 01:15:51.427
<i>I couldn't believe it. Of all people.</i>

1349
01:15:51.668 --> 01:15:54.580
<i>She gave up everybody.</i>
<i>Jimmy. me. Even her brother.</i>

1350
01:15:54.668 --> 01:15:56.067
[Bookie's sister sobs]

1351
01:15:56.148 --> 01:15:59.026
HENRY: <i>It took the jury six hours</i>
<i>to bring us in guilty.</i>

1352
01:15:59.108 --> 01:16:01.906
<i>The judge gave us ten years.</i>
<i>like he was giving away candy.</i>

1353
01:16:01.988 --> 01:16:04.502
JUDGE: Ten years in a federal penitentiary.

1354
01:16:05.028 --> 01:16:06.939
JUDGE: You will now be turned over...

1355
01:16:07.028 --> 01:16:08.825
...to the U.S. Attorney General.

1356
01:16:08.908 --> 01:16:10.341
[Gavel bangs]

1357
01:16:11.628 --> 01:16:13.186
MORRIE: Well. sweet Henry...

1358
01:16:13.268 --> 01:16:16.419
Toast. guys. Good trip. good life.
Get out soon.

1359
01:16:17.508 --> 01:16:19.339
Good trip. sweetheart.

1360
01:16:19.508 --> 01:16:21.658
[Glasses clink. toasts exchanged]

1361
01:16:21.988 --> 01:16:24.104
MORRIE: We'll watch the home front.

1362
01:16:25.268 --> 01:16:27.657
TOMMY: Say hello to those blow-job hacks.

1363
01:16:28.708 --> 01:16:31.176
TOMMY: Motherfuck them
every chance you get.

1364
01:16:31.268 --> 01:16:32.587
[Laughter]

1365
01:16:37.108 --> 01:16:39.542
HENRY: I'll call you when I get a chance.

1366
01:16:49.148 --> 01:16:50.627
[Henry coughs]

1367
01:16:51.828 --> 01:16:52.943
Now take me to jail.

1368
01:16:57.268 --> 01:16:59.987
HENRY:
<i>In prison. dinner was always a big thing.</i>

1369
01:17:00.388 --> 01:17:03.698
<i>We had a pasta course.</i>
<i>then we had a meat or a fish.</i>

1370
01:17:03.988 --> 01:17:06.866
<i>Paulie did the prep work.</i>
<i>He was doing a year for contempt...</i>

1371
01:17:06.948 --> 01:17:09.382
<i>... and had a wonderful system for garlic.</i>

1372
01:17:09.748 --> 01:17:12.387
<i>He used a razor and sliced it so thin...</i>

1373
01:17:12.548 --> 01:17:15.426
<i>... it would liquefy in the pan</i>
<i>with a little oil.</i>

1374
01:17:15.668 --> 01:17:17.386
<i>It was a very good system.</i>

1375
01:17:17.748 --> 01:17:20.137
<i>Vinnie was in charge of the tomato sauce.</i>

1376
01:17:20.468 --> 01:17:22.106
VINNIE: Get that smell?

1377
01:17:22.388 --> 01:17:26.063
Three kinds of meat in the meatballs:
Veal. beef. and pork.

1378
01:17:26.708 --> 01:17:28.539
JIMMY: You got to have pork.

1379
01:17:29.028 --> 01:17:30.461
VINNIE: That's the flavor.

1380
01:17:30.548 --> 01:17:34.541
HENRY: <i>I felt he used too many onions.</i>
<i>but it was still a very good sauce.</i>

1381
01:17:34.868 --> 01:17:36.938
Don't put too many onions in the sauce.

1382
01:17:37.028 --> 01:17:39.622
VINNIE: I didn't put
too much onions in. Paul.

1383
01:17:39.748 --> 01:17:41.739
VINNIE: There are only three small onions.

1384
01:17:41.828 --> 01:17:43.978
JOHNNY: Three onions?
How many tomatoes?

1385
01:17:44.068 --> 01:17:47.026
VINNIE: Two big cans.
JOHNNY: You don't need three onions.

1386
01:17:47.108 --> 01:17:48.700
HENRY: <i>Johnny Dio did the meat.</i>

1387
01:17:48.788 --> 01:17:51.507
<i>We had no broiler.</i>
<i>so he did everything in pans.</i>

1388
01:17:51.748 --> 01:17:54.785
<i>It smelled up the joint and</i>
<i>the hacks used to die...</i>

1389
01:17:55.028 --> 01:17:56.859
<i>... but he cooked a great steak.</i>

1390
01:17:56.948 --> 01:17:59.826
JOHNNY: How do you like yours?
VINNIE: Medium rare.

1391
01:18:00.148 --> 01:18:02.298
JOHNNY: Medium rare. An aristocrat.

1392
01:18:02.788 --> 01:18:06.258
HENRY: <i>When you think of prison</i>
<i>you get pictures in your mind...</i>

1393
01:18:06.388 --> 01:18:09.903
<i>... of all those old movies with rows</i>
<i>and rows of guys behind bars.</i>

1394
01:18:09.988 --> 01:18:12.058
<i>It wasn't like that for wiseguys.</i>

1395
01:18:12.308 --> 01:18:15.983
<i>It wasn't bad. but I missed Jimmy.</i>
<i>who was doing his time in Atlanta.</i>

1396
01:18:16.068 --> 01:18:17.786
JOHNNY: Give me two steaks.

1397
01:18:19.108 --> 01:18:22.578
HENRY: <i>Everyone else in the joint</i>
<i>was doing real time. all together...</i>

1398
01:18:22.668 --> 01:18:24.306
<i>... living like pigs.</i>

1399
01:18:24.388 --> 01:18:27.027
<i>But we lived alone. We owned the joint.</i>

1400
01:18:27.108 --> 01:18:30.384
JOHNNY: We batted them sons of bitches.
You couldn't recognize them.

1401
01:18:30.468 --> 01:18:31.901
VINNIE: They deserved it.

1402
01:18:31.988 --> 01:18:35.298
<i>Even the hacks we couldn't bribe</i>
<i>wouldn't rat on the guys we did.</i>

1403
01:18:35.388 --> 01:18:38.141
JOHNNY: People used to be able
to leave their doors open.

1404
01:18:38.228 --> 01:18:41.618
Sorry it took so long.
That skinny guard's a pain in the ass.

1405
01:18:41.708 --> 01:18:43.778
PAUL: We have to take care
of that bastard.

1406
01:18:43.868 --> 01:18:45.267
HENRY: I took care of him.

1407
01:18:45.348 --> 01:18:46.986
PAUL: What'd you bring?

1408
01:18:47.348 --> 01:18:48.747
HENRY: Some bread.

1409
01:18:49.188 --> 01:18:51.338
HENRY: Vinnie. I got peppers and onions.

1410
01:18:51.428 --> 01:18:53.862
HENRY: Salami. prosciutto. a lot of cheese.

1411
01:18:53.948 --> 01:18:55.017
What else?

1412
01:18:55.348 --> 01:18:57.020
HENRY: Scotch.
PAUL: Nice.

1413
01:18:57.588 --> 01:18:58.907
- Red wine.
- Okay.

1414
01:18:59.828 --> 01:19:01.898
- Now we can eat.
- Some white. too.

1415
01:19:02.628 --> 01:19:06.303
PAUL: Beautiful. Okay. boys. let's eat.
Come on. Johnny. Vinnie.

1416
01:19:08.068 --> 01:19:11.378
PAUL: Tomorrow we eat sandwiches.
You got to go on a diet. Vinnie.

1417
01:19:11.468 --> 01:19:13.186
[Continued conversation]

1418
01:19:17.828 --> 01:19:19.261
PAUL: Read 'em and weep.

1419
01:19:19.348 --> 01:19:20.827
[Group laughs]

1420
01:19:21.908 --> 01:19:23.580
PAUL: What are you doing?

1421
01:19:32.628 --> 01:19:34.698
HENRY: I'll catch you guys later.

1422
01:19:34.788 --> 01:19:36.904
PAUL: Going for a walk in the park?

1423
01:19:39.028 --> 01:19:42.100
DRUG BUYER: I'll catch you next week.
HENRY: Thanks.

1424
01:19:44.308 --> 01:19:47.459
- Is there any more?
- No. that's it. Have a good weekend.

1425
01:19:48.028 --> 01:19:50.178
[Buzzer sounds. indistinct chatter]

1426
01:20:02.068 --> 01:20:04.138
KAREN: You girls stay right here.

1427
01:20:04.228 --> 01:20:06.742
KAREN: Hold hands.
GUARD: Go right up front.

1428
01:20:09.228 --> 01:20:12.186
GUARD: How are you doing?
KAREN: Good. How are you?

1429
01:20:23.428 --> 01:20:24.383
What?

1430
01:20:24.468 --> 01:20:26.538
I saw her name on the register.

1431
01:20:27.028 --> 01:20:28.620
KAREN: Want her to visit you?

1432
01:20:28.708 --> 01:20:31.984
Let her stay up all night crying
and writing to the parole board.

1433
01:20:32.068 --> 01:20:35.105
What am I doing here?
Where am I? I'm in jail.

1434
01:20:35.348 --> 01:20:37.498
I can't stop people from visiting me.

1435
01:20:37.588 --> 01:20:40.625
Let her sneak this stuff
in for you every week.

1436
01:20:40.708 --> 01:20:41.857
[Ruth crying]

1437
01:20:41.948 --> 01:20:43.904
Let her fight these bastards every week!

1438
01:20:43.988 --> 01:20:46.058
Look what you're doing! Stop it!

1439
01:20:46.388 --> 01:20:47.741
KAREN: I'm sorry.

1440
01:20:48.148 --> 01:20:50.264
Let her sneak this shit in for you.

1441
01:20:52.148 --> 01:20:53.740
HENRY: Will you stop it?

1442
01:20:53.988 --> 01:20:56.138
KAREN: Let her do it!
HENRY: Stop it!

1443
01:20:58.148 --> 01:20:59.422
[Ruth crying]

1444
01:20:59.508 --> 01:21:01.976
HENRY: Shh. Ruth. Ruth. come here.

1445
01:21:04.068 --> 01:21:06.662
KAREN: Nobody's helping me.
I am all alone.

1446
01:21:08.308 --> 01:21:10.299
Belle and Morrie are broke.

1447
01:21:10.708 --> 01:21:13.745
I asked your friend Remo
for the money he owes you.

1448
01:21:14.228 --> 01:21:18.744
He told me to take the kids down
to the police station and get on welfare.

1449
01:21:19.028 --> 01:21:20.700
It's going to be okay.

1450
01:21:20.948 --> 01:21:24.702
I've never seen Paulie since he got out.
I never see anyone.

1451
01:21:25.428 --> 01:21:28.022
That's what happens when you go away.

1452
01:21:28.708 --> 01:21:32.223
We're on our own. Forget everybody else.
Forget Paulie.

1453
01:21:32.788 --> 01:21:36.303
As long as he's on parole
he doesn't want anybody doing anything.

1454
01:21:39.188 --> 01:21:41.304
KAREN: I can't do it.
HENRY: Yes. you can.

1455
01:21:41.388 --> 01:21:43.822
All I need is for you to bring me this stuff.

1456
01:21:43.908 --> 01:21:46.706
A guy in here from Pittsburgh
will help me move it.

1457
01:21:46.788 --> 01:21:49.507
In a month we'll be fine.
We won't need anybody.

1458
01:21:49.668 --> 01:21:50.783
KAREN: I'm afraid.

1459
01:21:50.868 --> 01:21:52.699
I'm afraid if Paulie finds out...

1460
01:21:52.788 --> 01:21:54.779
He is not helping us out.

1461
01:21:55.108 --> 01:21:57.258
Is he putting any food on the table?

1462
01:21:58.708 --> 01:22:00.539
We've got to help each other.

1463
01:22:00.788 --> 01:22:04.064
We got to be really.
really careful while we do it.

1464
01:22:08.308 --> 01:22:10.458
I don't want to hear about her anymore.

1465
01:22:10.548 --> 01:22:11.503
Never.

1466
01:22:19.828 --> 01:22:21.227
[Door slams]

1467
01:22:35.988 --> 01:22:37.706
RUTH & JUDY: Daddy!

1468
01:22:38.948 --> 01:22:41.257
JUDY: We missed you.
RUTH: Are you here to stay?

1469
01:22:41.348 --> 01:22:44.784
JUDY: Did you see our pictures?
I did the one with the house and rainbow.

1470
01:22:44.868 --> 01:22:46.301
RUTH: I did the sun.

1471
01:22:46.548 --> 01:22:49.745
JUDY: My chorus concert is in two weeks.
Are you coming?

1472
01:22:50.948 --> 01:22:52.779
JUDY: Do you like the house?

1473
01:22:53.988 --> 01:22:56.821
- Get packed. We're moving out.
- With what?

1474
01:22:57.268 --> 01:23:00.226
Don't worry.
Just start looking for a new house.

1475
01:23:00.468 --> 01:23:03.426
I got to go to Pittsburgh.
Those guys owe me $15.000.

1476
01:23:03.588 --> 01:23:05.738
We'll be okay. I got things lined up.

1477
01:23:05.828 --> 01:23:08.547
Pittsburgh? You have to see
your parole officer.

1478
01:23:08.628 --> 01:23:10.141
Don't worry about it.

1479
01:23:10.388 --> 01:23:13.664
Everything will be fine.
Who wants to go to Uncle Paulie's?

1480
01:23:13.748 --> 01:23:15.340
RUTH & JUDY: Me!

1481
01:23:15.428 --> 01:23:17.817
[Big band tune plays. background]

1482
01:23:19.188 --> 01:23:21.065
[Scattered conversation]

1483
01:23:23.988 --> 01:23:25.580
What do you want?

1484
01:23:25.908 --> 01:23:28.217
PAUL'S WIFE: Sweetheart. let Mommy eat.

1485
01:23:31.348 --> 01:23:34.306
You look good.
Did you eat this good in the joint?

1486
01:23:35.868 --> 01:23:37.984
PAUL: I don't want any more of that shit.

1487
01:23:38.068 --> 01:23:41.902
HENRY: What are you talking about?
PAUL: Just stay away from the garbage.

1488
01:23:41.988 --> 01:23:44.377
Inside. you did what you had to do.

1489
01:23:44.628 --> 01:23:47.381
I'm talking about now. From here and now.

1490
01:23:48.628 --> 01:23:51.096
- Why would I get into that?
- Don't make a jerk of me.

1491
01:23:51.188 --> 01:23:52.621
Just don't do it.

1492
01:23:53.428 --> 01:23:54.543
Don't do it.

1493
01:23:56.388 --> 01:23:59.027
I want to talk about Jimmy.
Watch out for him.

1494
01:23:59.428 --> 01:24:02.226
He's a good earner.
but he takes too many chances.

1495
01:24:02.468 --> 01:24:04.538
I wouldn't take chances like Jimmy.

1496
01:24:04.708 --> 01:24:08.223
Tommy's a good kid. but he's crazy.
He's got too much to prove.

1497
01:24:08.548 --> 01:24:12.063
- You got to watch out for them.
- I only use them for certain things.

1498
01:24:12.148 --> 01:24:14.901
I ain't going to get fucked like Gribbs.

1499
01:24:15.428 --> 01:24:19.262
Gribbs is 70 years old and he'll
die in prison. I don't need that.

1500
01:24:19.908 --> 01:24:23.184
So I'm warning everybody.
Could be my son. could be anybody.

1501
01:24:24.148 --> 01:24:28.380
Gribbs got 20 years just for saying hello
to some fuck who was selling junk.

1502
01:24:28.788 --> 01:24:31.177
That won't happen to me. understand?

1503
01:24:31.428 --> 01:24:33.737
You're out early because I got you a job.

1504
01:24:33.828 --> 01:24:35.466
I don't need this heat.

1505
01:24:35.668 --> 01:24:38.057
You see anybody with shit you tell me.

1506
01:24:39.588 --> 01:24:40.543
Anybody.

1507
01:24:40.828 --> 01:24:42.546
HENRY: All right.
PAUL: Yeah?

1508
01:24:42.628 --> 01:24:43.947
Yeah. Of course.

1509
01:24:44.468 --> 01:24:46.936
[Upbeat rock song plays. background]

1510
01:24:50.428 --> 01:24:54.057
HENRY: <i>It took me a week of sneaking</i>
<i>around to unload the Pittsburgh stuff.</i>

1511
01:24:54.148 --> 01:24:56.582
<i>But when I did. it was a real score.</i>

1512
01:24:57.028 --> 01:24:59.462
<i>I used Sandy's place to mix the stuff.</i>

1513
01:24:59.748 --> 01:25:04.378
<i>Even with Sandy snorting more than she</i>
<i>mixed. I saw this was a good business.</i>

1514
01:25:04.748 --> 01:25:07.137
<i>I made $12.000 in my second week.</i>

1515
01:25:07.588 --> 01:25:10.739
<i>I had a down payment on my house</i>
<i>and things were rolling.</i>

1516
01:25:10.948 --> 01:25:14.179
<i>All I had to do was once in a while</i>
<i>tell Sandy I loved her.</i>

1517
01:25:18.468 --> 01:25:19.981
<i>It was perfect.</i>

1518
01:25:20.428 --> 01:25:24.421
<i>As long as I got the stuff from Pittsburgh.</i>
<i>Paulie would never find out.</i>

1519
01:25:24.708 --> 01:25:28.337
<i>Within a couple of weeks</i>
<i>it got so big I needed some help.</i>

1520
01:25:28.868 --> 01:25:31.063
<i>I got Jimmy and Tommy</i>
<i>to come in with me.</i>

1521
01:25:31.148 --> 01:25:33.423
JIMMY: Nice.
TOMMY: It's fucking great.

1522
01:25:33.548 --> 01:25:35.459
PAROLE OFFICER: Conway.

1523
01:25:35.628 --> 01:25:37.425
[Rock song continues]

1524
01:25:40.228 --> 01:25:42.617
PAROLE OFFICER:
You bring your pay slips?

1525
01:25:45.188 --> 01:25:47.463
KAREN: Four and a half months of dirt.

1526
01:25:47.908 --> 01:25:49.864
BELLE: It's so good.
KAREN: I did it.

1527
01:25:49.948 --> 01:25:51.222
[Karen chuckles]

1528
01:25:51.308 --> 01:25:53.868
KAREN: Do you love it?
BELLE: It's wonderful.

1529
01:25:54.308 --> 01:25:57.698
KAREN: This we had to have made special.
Go ahead. sit in it.

1530
01:25:57.988 --> 01:26:00.502
KAREN: The others you couldn't even sit in.

1531
01:26:00.708 --> 01:26:02.107
KAREN: Okay. ready?

1532
01:26:02.468 --> 01:26:04.538
Watch the wall with the rock.

1533
01:26:05.628 --> 01:26:07.266
[Electrical hiss]

1534
01:26:08.388 --> 01:26:09.662
[All laugh]

1535
01:26:11.268 --> 01:26:14.101
KAREN: The electricians did it special.
Come on.

1536
01:26:16.748 --> 01:26:21.026
This was imported. It came in two pieces.
Do you believe what they can do?

1537
01:26:21.228 --> 01:26:22.377
HENRY: Nice. huh?

1538
01:26:22.468 --> 01:26:24.584
Come here. Did you and Jimmy talk?

1539
01:26:24.708 --> 01:26:26.903
He's looking into everything.

1540
01:26:27.108 --> 01:26:29.861
It'll make the Air France hold
look like peanuts.

1541
01:26:30.188 --> 01:26:31.143
Come on.

1542
01:26:31.308 --> 01:26:33.344
- He'll do it. right?
- I told you.

1543
01:26:33.548 --> 01:26:37.018
He's looking into it.
We'll see what happens. No promises.

1544
01:26:37.868 --> 01:26:40.826
Do you understand?
There's millions in there.

1545
01:26:41.188 --> 01:26:44.578
I've been cultivating this
son of a bitch for two years.

1546
01:26:44.868 --> 01:26:48.463
He owes me 20 grand.
Once in a lifetime. I could retire.

1547
01:26:48.708 --> 01:26:52.542
No more nut every week.
No more bullshit. My dream comes true.

1548
01:26:52.748 --> 01:26:54.101
Let's get a drink.

1549
01:26:54.228 --> 01:26:57.698
HENRY: <i>These are the guys Jimmy put</i>
<i>together for what turned out to be...</i>

1550
01:26:57.788 --> 01:27:01.622
<i>... the biggest heist in American history.</i>
<i>The Lufthansa heist.</i>

1551
01:27:02.468 --> 01:27:06.780
<i>Tommy and Carbone would grab the guard</i>
<i>and make him get us in the front door.</i>

1552
01:27:06.868 --> 01:27:08.665
FRENCHY: Louisiana Lightning!

1553
01:27:08.748 --> 01:27:11.899
HENRY: <i>Frenchy and Joe Buddha</i>
<i>had to round up the workers.</i>

1554
01:27:12.428 --> 01:27:16.182
<i>Johnny Roastbeef kept them</i>
<i>tied up and away from the alarms.</i>

1555
01:27:17.028 --> 01:27:19.098
<i>Even Stacks Edwards got in on it.</i>

1556
01:27:19.268 --> 01:27:22.783
<i>He used to play guitar at the lounge.</i>
<i>Everybody loved Stacks.</i>

1557
01:27:22.988 --> 01:27:25.104
<i>He was supposed to steal the panel truck...</i>

1558
