02:09:20.828 --> 02:09:24.741
<i>That's when I knew I would never</i>
<i>have come back from Florida alive.</i>

2188
02:09:27.308 --> 02:09:29.299
[Henry clears his throat]

2189
02:09:37.308 --> 02:09:40.664
Wherever you move me.
I asked once and I'll tell you again...

2190
02:09:40.828 --> 02:09:43.058
...I don't want to go any place cold.

2191
02:09:43.868 --> 02:09:45.620
You don't have a choice.

2192
02:09:46.348 --> 02:09:49.101
Come on. Whoever fucking controls it...

2193
02:09:49.548 --> 02:09:51.937
...just no place cold. Do that for me.

2194
02:09:52.188 --> 02:09:54.179
He's bronchial. that's why.

2195
02:09:54.428 --> 02:09:56.817
If he's bronchial we'll consider that.

2196
02:09:56.988 --> 02:09:58.819
I'd like to go someplace not cold.

2197
02:09:58.908 --> 02:10:02.218
Can I ask you some questions?
What about my parents?

2198
02:10:03.668 --> 02:10:04.737
What about them?

2199
02:10:04.828 --> 02:10:08.104
Am I going to see them?
Am I going to talk to them?

2200
02:10:08.348 --> 02:10:10.862
Don't I have some kind of contact
with them?

2201
02:10:11.228 --> 02:10:12.183
No.

2202
02:10:13.308 --> 02:10:16.664
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.
You mean to tell me...

2203
02:10:16.908 --> 02:10:20.901
...if something happens to my parents
and they get sick. I can't see them?

2204
02:10:20.988 --> 02:10:23.866
Maybe something can be worked out
if they're sick.

2205
02:10:24.108 --> 02:10:26.668
If there's extraordinary circumstances...

2206
02:10:26.908 --> 02:10:29.706
I can't do this. I can't do this. Henry.

2207
02:10:30.348 --> 02:10:32.339
I can't leave my parents.

2208
02:10:33.628 --> 02:10:35.619
HENRY: Karen. I told you before.

2209
02:10:36.508 --> 02:10:39.898
I'm not going to do this unless
you and the kids come with me.

2210
02:10:41.548 --> 02:10:43.539
I can't do it without you.

2211
02:10:43.788 --> 02:10:46.302
So you do whatever. but... that's it.

2212
02:10:48.588 --> 02:10:51.705
KAREN: You need Henry. not me. right?
EDWARD: That's right.

2213
02:10:51.788 --> 02:10:53.858
I don't care whether you go or not.

2214
02:10:54.428 --> 02:10:57.704
If it'll make him a better witness.
I want you with him.

2215
02:10:57.948 --> 02:10:59.461
They don't want me.

2216
02:10:59.548 --> 02:11:03.302
EDWARD: Henry'll be in the protection
program. They can't get to him.

2217
02:11:03.388 --> 02:11:06.585
They can only get to him
by getting to you or your kids.

2218
02:11:06.748 --> 02:11:09.023
If he goes into the program
you're in danger.

2219
02:11:09.108 --> 02:11:11.702
KAREN: I don't know anything.
EDWARD: Don't give me...

2220
02:11:11.788 --> 02:11:13.301
...the babe-in-the-woods routine.

2221
02:11:13.388 --> 02:11:17.540
I've listened to those wiretaps
and I've heard you talk about cocaine.

2222
02:11:17.788 --> 02:11:21.701
EDWARD: Conversation after conversation
you talked to Henry on the phone.

2223
02:11:25.948 --> 02:11:28.587
It doesn't matter.
Whether he goes to jail...

2224
02:11:28.748 --> 02:11:31.387
...or stays on the streets. he's a dead man.

2225
02:11:31.948 --> 02:11:33.779
He knows it and you know it.

2226
02:11:35.068 --> 02:11:37.343
HENRY: What about the kids and school?

2227
02:11:37.788 --> 02:11:39.619
KAREN: I mean. what goes on?

2228
02:11:39.828 --> 02:11:42.023
TUDDY: Go to Wall Street
and get real crooks.

2229
02:11:42.108 --> 02:11:44.417
Whoever sold you those suits
had a sense of humor.

2230
02:11:44.508 --> 02:11:47.784
What it comes down to is
we're your only salvation.

2231
02:11:48.188 --> 02:11:51.863
We'll save your life. his life.
and we'll keep you out of jail.

2232
02:11:54.988 --> 02:11:57.946
EDWARD: This morning you told the jury
about your background.

2233
02:11:58.028 --> 02:12:00.337
HENRY: <i>It was easy for us to disappear.</i>

2234
02:12:00.588 --> 02:12:04.740
<i>My house was in my mother-in-law's name.</i>
<i>My cars were registered to my wife.</i>

2235
02:12:04.908 --> 02:12:08.184
<i>My Social Security cards</i>
<i>and driver's licenses were phonies.</i>

2236
02:12:08.428 --> 02:12:10.578
<i>I never voted or paid taxes.</i>

2237
02:12:11.068 --> 02:12:14.902
<i>My birth certificate and arrest sheet</i>
<i>were all that showed I was alive.</i>

2238
02:12:14.988 --> 02:12:17.343
EDWARD: Do you see him here
in this courtroom?

2239
02:12:17.428 --> 02:12:18.258
Yes.

2240
02:12:18.348 --> 02:12:21.226
EDWARD: Will you please point him
out for the jury?

2241
02:12:23.148 --> 02:12:27.539
EDWARD: Let the record show that Mr. Hill
identified the defendant. James Conway.

2242
02:12:29.148 --> 02:12:31.537
EDWARD: Do you also know a man
named Paul Cicero?

2243
02:12:31.628 --> 02:12:34.188
EDWARD: Is he in the courtroom?
HENRY: Yes.

2244
02:12:34.268 --> 02:12:36.736
EDWARD: Can you point him out
for the jury?

2245
02:12:37.468 --> 02:12:41.541
EDWARD: Let the record show Mr. Hill
identified the defendant Paul Cicero.

2246
02:12:43.308 --> 02:12:45.060
EDWARD: I have a document...

2247
02:12:45.148 --> 02:12:47.821
HENRY: <i>The hardest thing was</i>
<i>leaving the life.</i>

2248
02:12:48.348 --> 02:12:49.986
<i>I still loved the life.</i>

2249
02:12:50.108 --> 02:12:53.896
<i>We were treated like movie stars</i>
<i>with muscle. We had it all.</i>

2250
02:12:54.428 --> 02:12:57.465
<i>Our wives. mothers. kids.</i>
<i>everybody rode along.</i>

2251
02:12:57.868 --> 02:13:01.144
<i>I had paper bags filled with jewelry</i>
<i>stashed in the kitchen.</i>

2252
02:13:01.228 --> 02:13:03.298
<i>I had a bowl of coke next to my bed.</i>

2253
02:13:03.388 --> 02:13:06.937
HAYES: People call them rats because
they will do anything to survive.

2254
02:13:07.028 --> 02:13:09.064
EDWARD: Objection!
JUDGE: Objection sustained.

2255
02:13:09.148 --> 02:13:13.300
HENRY: I know nothing about being a rat.
HAYES: You know everything about it!

2256
02:13:14.588 --> 02:13:16.897
HENRY: <i>Anything I wanted was</i>
<i>a phone call away.</i>

2257
02:13:16.988 --> 02:13:20.264
<i>Free cars. Keys to a dozen hideouts</i>
<i>all over the city.</i>

2258
02:13:20.508 --> 02:13:22.942
<i>I'd bet 20 grand over a weekend...</i>

2259
02:13:23.148 --> 02:13:27.061
<i>... then blow the winnings in a week</i>
<i>or go to sharks to pay the bookies.</i>

2260
02:13:27.308 --> 02:13:28.661
Didn't matter.

2261
02:13:28.988 --> 02:13:33.140
It didn't mean anything. When I was broke
I would go rob some more.

2262
02:13:33.948 --> 02:13:35.620
We ran everything.

2263
02:13:35.948 --> 02:13:39.623
We paid off cops. We paid off lawyers.
We paid off judges.

2264
02:13:40.188 --> 02:13:43.976
Everybody had their hands out.
Everything was for the taking.

2265
02:13:45.468 --> 02:13:47.106
And now it's all over.

2266
02:13:47.708 --> 02:13:49.664
HENRY: <i>That's the hardest part.</i>

2267
02:13:50.428 --> 02:13:52.180
<i>Today everything is different.</i>

2268
02:13:52.268 --> 02:13:56.022
<i>There's no action. I have to wait around</i>
<i>like everyone else.</i>

2269
02:13:56.508 --> 02:13:58.499
<i>Can't even get decent food.</i>

2270
02:13:58.748 --> 02:14:01.979
<i>After I got here I ordered spaghetti</i>
<i>with marinara sauce...</i>

2271
02:14:02.108 --> 02:14:04.338
<i>... and I got egg noodles and ketchup.</i>

2272
02:14:04.428 --> 02:14:06.259
<i>I'm an average nobody.</i>

2273
02:14:07.148 --> 02:14:10.026
<i>I get to live the rest of my life</i>
<i>like a schnook.</i>

2274
02:14:11.748 --> 02:14:13.067
[Gunshots]

2275
02:14:13.988 --> 02:14:16.582
[Fast-paced rock song plays. background]

2276
02:15:27.548 --> 02:15:29.504
Subtitles : Filou ;-)
